00:26.859 --> 00:28.459
♪ Give me some rope ♪

00:28.493 --> 00:30.195
♪ tie me to dream ♪

00:30.229 --> 00:31.629
♪ give me the hope ♪

00:31.663 --> 00:33.331
♪ to run out of steam ♪

00:33.365 --> 00:36.835
♪ somebody said
it can be here ♪

00:36.869 --> 00:38.469
♪ we could be roped up ♪

00:38.503 --> 00:40.771
♪ tied up, dead in a year ♪

00:40.806 --> 00:45.609
♪ I can't count the reasons
I should stay ♪

00:45.644 --> 00:49.314
♪ one by one,
they all just fade away ♪

00:49.348 --> 00:52.851
♪ ♪

00:52.885 --> 00:56.487
Okay, this awkward silence
has been going on for days.

00:56.521 --> 00:58.522
Granted, Jeffrey looks amazing
when he broods,

00:58.557 --> 01:00.424
but this has got to stop.

01:00.459 --> 01:02.861
Now, I don't know
what happened,

01:02.895 --> 01:06.331
but we have to get
to the bottom of this.

01:06.365 --> 01:07.598
It's too embarrassing.

01:07.666 --> 01:09.100
I understand.

01:09.134 --> 01:10.668
You don't wanna talk about it,

01:10.702 --> 01:12.670
and you won't have to.

01:12.704 --> 01:16.274
They will talk <i>for</i> you.

01:16.308 --> 01:18.642
Why did you make, have,
and bring these?

01:18.677 --> 01:19.744
- Mm.
- Don't answer.

01:19.778 --> 01:21.346
- It's puppet therapy.
- Mm-hmm.

01:21.380 --> 01:23.348
The psychology world
has recently embraced it

01:23.382 --> 01:25.016
after seeing it on <i>Law & Order.</i>

01:25.050 --> 01:27.051
You'll notice that each puppet
is made in your likeness.

01:27.086 --> 01:28.353
They were a rush job.

01:28.387 --> 01:31.189
It's not like I had them
on hand for personal use.

01:31.223 --> 01:32.757
[Chuckles]
Excuse me.

01:32.791 --> 01:36.494
Let me just grab this thing
that's definitely not a whip.

01:36.528 --> 01:38.363
In addition to being adorable,

01:38.397 --> 01:40.365
I know firsthand
that puppet therapy

01:40.399 --> 01:41.799
can and does work.

01:41.833 --> 01:43.401
Uh, Dean,
puppet Kevin here thinks

01:43.435 --> 01:44.969
I should have a candy bar
right now.

01:45.004 --> 01:47.438
No, you know
how it winds you up.

01:47.472 --> 01:48.806
Fine.
We'll split it.

01:48.840 --> 01:50.808
All right.
Got money, bro?

01:50.842 --> 01:52.643
He's not what he seems!

01:52.677 --> 01:54.645
Wait.
Where's Pierce?

01:54.679 --> 01:57.415
I know he's not with us,
but is he still with us?

01:57.449 --> 01:58.849
I'm sure he's fine.

01:58.884 --> 01:59.984
Although, no one's seen him

02:00.019 --> 02:02.086
since he lost his mind
in the woods.

02:02.121 --> 02:03.821
You all were in the woods?
Oh.

02:03.855 --> 02:05.456
Oh, so the puppets are working.
Okay.

02:05.490 --> 02:06.690
Uh...
[Chuckles]

02:06.725 --> 02:08.459
How did it start?
What happened?

02:08.493 --> 02:09.460
We're not playing with puppets.

02:09.494 --> 02:10.693
Oh, Jeffrey.

02:10.762 --> 02:12.964
Dean, what happened
is between us and Jesus,

02:12.998 --> 02:14.299
and Jesus don't snitch.

02:14.333 --> 02:15.934
Yeah, and I don't need
a puppet to express myself.

02:15.968 --> 02:17.302
I already say whatever I want.

02:17.336 --> 02:19.770
But I am a fan
of the medium, so...

02:19.805 --> 02:20.905
my father is withholding.

02:20.940 --> 02:22.440
- Ow.
- Hm.

02:22.474 --> 02:23.507
That's interesting.

02:23.542 --> 02:25.176
Guys, are we just gonna avoid

02:25.210 --> 02:26.610
making eye contact forever?

02:26.645 --> 02:27.578
Who are we, Jeff during sex?

02:27.612 --> 02:28.779
Both: Huh?

02:28.814 --> 02:30.915
Let's just give it a shot
and move on.

02:30.950 --> 02:31.950
Fine.

02:31.984 --> 02:33.451
If we're gonna play this game,

02:33.485 --> 02:35.420
then, unlike sex with Britta,

02:35.454 --> 02:36.520
we're gonna do it quickly

02:36.555 --> 02:38.156
and with a small shred
of dignity.

02:38.190 --> 02:39.857
- Eh.
- Yeah.

02:39.891 --> 02:42.327
Jeffrey, dignity
is my middle name,

02:42.361 --> 02:44.728
and my first name is

02:44.763 --> 02:48.266
Dean-nocchio!

02:48.300 --> 02:52.203
[Mimics grand entrance music]

02:55.707 --> 02:58.009
- Whoo.
- It all started on Friday.

02:58.043 --> 03:00.011
Britta was talking about a few
of her latest causes.

03:00.045 --> 03:01.946
This one's for the Greendale
animal shelter,

03:01.981 --> 03:03.481
this one's for global warming,

03:03.515 --> 03:04.815
this one's for global cooling,

03:04.850 --> 03:06.951
and this one's
for the amount of rubber wasted

03:06.986 --> 03:08.619
while making stupid bracelets.

03:08.653 --> 03:09.988
That's called rubber flubbing,

03:10.022 --> 03:11.522
and it's a real problem.

03:11.556 --> 03:12.957
Open your eyes, people!

03:12.992 --> 03:14.725
Britta said,
"Open your eyes, people."

03:14.759 --> 03:15.994
- Square.
- Nice.

03:16.028 --> 03:17.128
- What are you two doing?
- Oh.

03:17.162 --> 03:18.429
We're playing
"Study Group Bingo."

03:18.464 --> 03:19.597
Study group bingo?

03:19.631 --> 03:20.965
We've been best friends
for four years,

03:21.000 --> 03:23.134
so we've fallen into a
comfortable, repetitive pattern

03:23.168 --> 03:25.536
like humorous misunderstandings
on <i>Three's Company</i>

03:25.570 --> 03:27.372
or girls gossiping on
<i>Gossip Girl.</i>

03:27.406 --> 03:29.207
So to liven things up,
Troy and I made this bingo chart

03:29.241 --> 03:30.541
of the predictable things
we say.

03:30.575 --> 03:32.176
This game is gay.

03:32.211 --> 03:34.145
- Square.
- You're mocking us?

03:34.179 --> 03:35.779
That's not a very Christian
thing to do.

03:35.814 --> 03:36.780
- Square.
- Oh.

03:36.815 --> 03:38.015
Can we go back to studying now?

03:38.017 --> 03:40.351
Both: Square.
- I don't like this game.

03:40.386 --> 03:41.619
- Me neither.
- I think it's mean.

03:41.653 --> 03:42.820
- There's no point.
- Yeah, it's insulting.

03:42.854 --> 03:44.855
- Okay, stop.
All: Square.

03:44.890 --> 03:46.690
[Groans] Abed's right.

03:46.725 --> 03:49.127
We've had the same conversation
a million times.

03:49.161 --> 03:50.895
I guess we're kind of stuck
in a--

03:50.929 --> 03:52.263
All: Rut?
- Yes.

03:52.297 --> 03:53.597
But to be fair,
there's not many things

03:53.632 --> 03:54.598
you could be stuck in.

03:54.633 --> 03:55.900
- Elevators.
- Bad marriages.

03:55.934 --> 03:57.001
A peat bog.

03:57.036 --> 03:58.102
On a flight in the middle seat.

03:58.137 --> 03:59.170
- Time loops.
- The bottom of a well.

03:59.204 --> 04:00.438
- Your own emotions.
- Quicksand.

04:00.472 --> 04:02.040
[Overlapping dialogue]
[Exhales]

04:02.074 --> 04:03.908
Okay, stop!
All: Square.

04:03.942 --> 04:05.876
How did we get so predictable?

04:05.911 --> 04:09.414
And here is our
state-of-the-art 1989 library

04:09.448 --> 04:10.614
where--oh, look!

04:10.649 --> 04:12.450
It is my favorite study group.

04:12.484 --> 04:14.718
They all really typify
the diversity

04:14.753 --> 04:16.454
we have here at Greendale.

04:16.488 --> 04:18.721
Uh, ruggedly handsome
leading man...

04:18.757 --> 04:21.059
[Chuckles] a mom, an activist,

04:21.093 --> 04:23.528
a perfect student,
a lifelong learner,

04:23.562 --> 04:24.929
a sidekick, and Abed.

04:24.963 --> 04:25.963
Enough foreplay.

04:25.997 --> 04:27.231
It's time
to move this tour along

04:27.266 --> 04:30.168
to meet
my good friend Magnitude!

04:30.202 --> 04:32.336
Yeah, prepare
to be pop-popped!

04:32.371 --> 04:33.737
Aw, he's a national treasure.

04:33.772 --> 04:35.873
Look, the problem isn't us.

04:35.907 --> 04:37.175
We're awesome.

04:37.209 --> 04:39.077
The problem is Greendale.

04:39.111 --> 04:40.978
It's pulling our strings,
and we need a break.

04:41.012 --> 04:43.147
Yeah, our Ferris Bueller
needs a day off.

04:43.182 --> 04:45.116
Hey, whose dad
has a vintage Ferrari?

04:45.150 --> 04:47.851
Abed, a pop culture reference
is more of the same.

04:47.886 --> 04:49.587
We need to go big.

04:49.621 --> 04:50.988
We need an adventure!

04:51.022 --> 04:53.791
That's a good idea, Annie,
but there's one problem.

04:53.825 --> 04:54.959
Where would we go?

04:54.993 --> 04:58.496
[Light up-tempo rock]

04:58.530 --> 05:00.798
♪ Where,
where would we go? ♪

05:00.832 --> 05:04.302
♪ we can go anywhere
that you know ♪

05:04.336 --> 05:06.170
Both: ♪ Could we travel
through time? ♪

05:06.205 --> 05:08.038
♪ or maybe see France? ♪

05:08.073 --> 05:11.476
♪ or anywhere else
naked ladies will dance? ♪

05:11.510 --> 05:13.478
♪ Could we fly in a booth ♪

05:13.512 --> 05:18.382
♪ Could we go
to church camp? ♪

05:18.417 --> 05:20.551
♪ I'd rather stay
at Greendale ♪

05:20.586 --> 05:22.453
♪ Could we ride ♪

05:22.488 --> 05:26.790
♪ a hot air balloon? ♪

05:26.825 --> 05:29.360
All: ♪ Yes ♪
- ♪ Now, that's an adventure ♪

05:29.394 --> 05:30.961
♪ Well, we should go soon ♪

05:30.996 --> 05:33.797
♪ We can go anywhere
in a balloon ♪

05:33.832 --> 05:36.434
All: ♪ Yes ♪
- ♪ That's an adventure ♪

05:36.468 --> 05:37.901
♪ We can go high ♪

05:37.936 --> 05:40.904
♪ We can see anything
up in the sky ♪

05:40.939 --> 05:43.474
Both: ♪ Yes ♪
All: ♪ Now that's an adventure ♪

05:43.509 --> 05:45.209
♪ Pierce, bring your dentures ♪

05:45.244 --> 05:48.746
All: ♪ We're so thrilled
because soon ♪

05:48.780 --> 05:52.483
♪ we'll be
in a hot air balloon ♪

05:52.518 --> 05:55.953
All: ♪ Ah, ah, ah ♪

05:55.987 --> 05:58.055
♪ ah, ah, ah ♪

05:58.089 --> 06:01.125
Hey, guys.
♪ I'm the balloon guide ♪

06:01.160 --> 06:04.562
♪ Before we take off, I'm gonna
check the balloon ties ♪

06:04.596 --> 06:08.032
♪ look at the burner,
check out the basket ♪

06:08.066 --> 06:11.269
♪ if you have a question,
feel free to ask it ♪

06:11.303 --> 06:13.638
♪ could we go
to space? ♪

06:13.672 --> 06:18.309
♪ could we fly
to heaven? ♪

06:18.343 --> 06:20.278
♪ I'd rather fly to Vegas ♪

06:20.312 --> 06:22.446
♪ it's getting time ♪

06:22.481 --> 06:26.784
♪ to ride the balloon ♪

06:26.818 --> 06:29.153
All: ♪ Yes, now this is adventure ♪

06:29.188 --> 06:31.088
♪ about to go soon ♪

06:31.122 --> 06:34.024
♪ we're gonna go anywhere
in the balloon ♪

06:34.059 --> 06:36.394
Both: ♪ Yes ♪
All: ♪ this is adventure ♪

06:36.428 --> 06:38.262
♪ We're starting to fly ♪

06:38.297 --> 06:41.666
♪ We can see everything
here in the sky ♪

06:41.700 --> 06:43.568
♪ this is adventure ♪

06:43.602 --> 06:47.505
♪ there's beautiful weather
now outside ♪

06:47.539 --> 06:48.806
♪ and we're fine ♪

06:48.840 --> 06:53.311
♪ as long as we have
a balloon guide ♪

06:53.345 --> 06:54.412
- Uh...
- Oh, no!

06:54.446 --> 06:56.146
[Overlapping dialogue]

06:56.181 --> 06:57.381
Oh, boy.

06:57.416 --> 07:00.851
From now on,
no more singing in the balloon.

07:00.885 --> 07:03.120
- Did I miss it?
- Miss what?

07:03.154 --> 07:04.855
Who said anything
about a runaway balloon?

07:04.889 --> 07:07.592
Okay, let me process this.

07:07.626 --> 07:09.760
[Strained inhale]

07:09.794 --> 07:11.429
<i>No!</i>

07:11.463 --> 07:12.863
- Oh, God.
- Whoa, whoa.

07:12.897 --> 07:14.998
- We're really high.
- I'm really scared of heights.

07:15.033 --> 07:17.301
Guys, what are we gonna do?

07:17.336 --> 07:19.237
I had a dream
it would end this way.

07:19.271 --> 07:21.539
Oh, Jeffrey,
you're on a runaway balloon?

07:21.573 --> 07:23.941
You could have died.
You could have died.

07:23.975 --> 07:25.309
How could you almost
let him die?

07:25.344 --> 07:27.845
We all almost died,
but we all didn't.

07:27.879 --> 07:29.480
You know, plus,
a near death experience

07:29.481 --> 07:31.249
would've only brought us
closer together.

07:31.283 --> 07:33.117
Good point.

07:33.151 --> 07:34.911
Although it did
get pretty hairy after that

07:34.919 --> 07:36.854
especially once Pierce
started helping.

07:36.888 --> 07:39.557
Okay, everyone push down
with me at the same time.

07:39.591 --> 07:42.326
One, two, three!

07:42.361 --> 07:43.861
[Groans]

07:43.895 --> 07:46.196
Come on, people.
I can't do this alone.

07:46.231 --> 07:48.232
- You can't do it at all.
- [Groans]

07:48.267 --> 07:50.167
Oh, look.
A downstream.

07:50.201 --> 07:52.102
- [Gasps]
All: Pierce! No!

07:52.137 --> 07:54.672
Whoa!

07:54.706 --> 07:56.039
If we fly to heaven,

07:56.074 --> 07:58.609
please don't tell my grandpa
about me and Britta.

08:03.848 --> 08:05.982
[Indistinct dialogue]
This is not good.

08:06.731 --> 08:08.866
There are so many clouds.
It's so dark!

08:08.900 --> 08:11.201
I can't even see
the Landing Strip

08:11.235 --> 08:12.703
or any of the other nudie bars.

08:12.737 --> 08:14.572
Oh, heaven, help us.

08:14.606 --> 08:16.574
We must be a mile
above the ground.

08:16.608 --> 08:18.508
That's international airspace.

08:18.543 --> 08:20.444
We're literally above the law.

08:20.478 --> 08:22.012
Jeff can marry any man
he wants.

08:22.047 --> 08:23.480
Wait a second, guys.

08:23.514 --> 08:25.415
I think we're starting
to go down.

08:25.450 --> 08:27.117
You see?
Prayer works.

08:27.151 --> 08:28.819
So does gravity, Shirley.

08:28.853 --> 08:30.921
And you know
who invented gravity, right?

08:30.956 --> 08:33.090
All: Oh.
Whoa!

08:33.124 --> 08:34.191
Guys, let's put a pin

08:34.225 --> 08:35.705
in the mysteries
of the universe convo

08:35.727 --> 08:36.794
until we land.

08:36.828 --> 08:38.227
Which will be sooner
than we thought.

08:38.261 --> 08:39.563
We're gaining
speed fast, people.

08:39.597 --> 08:40.764
Oh!
Brace for impact.

08:40.799 --> 08:43.533
- Oh, damn you, gravity!
- Damn you, prayer!

08:43.568 --> 08:44.835
Damn you, Vicki!

08:44.869 --> 08:47.972
[All scream]

08:48.006 --> 08:49.239
Has anyone else noticed
Professor Duncan

08:49.273 --> 08:51.341
hasn't been around
for a long time?

08:51.375 --> 08:54.712
[All scream]

08:54.746 --> 08:56.513
Maybe I can soften our descent.

08:56.547 --> 08:57.514
Pierce, no!

08:57.548 --> 08:58.749
[Overlapping dialogue]

08:58.783 --> 09:01.685
Bring it to me strong,
old man monkey strength!

09:01.720 --> 09:04.755
[Overlapping dialogue]

09:04.789 --> 09:07.124
[Bird chirps]
Okay.

09:07.158 --> 09:09.994
Okay, obviously,
that was very scary.

09:10.028 --> 09:12.496
Post-traumatic stress
is a real issue,

09:12.530 --> 09:15.232
but with these puppets
giving voice to our feelings,

09:15.266 --> 09:16.667
we can begin to heal.

09:16.701 --> 09:17.968
Hey, come on.

09:18.003 --> 09:20.938
This is gonna be
a long and arduous process.

09:20.972 --> 09:22.139
There's more.

09:22.173 --> 09:23.641
Hey, well, excuse Dean

09:23.675 --> 09:26.977
for reacting to the natural lull
in your story.

09:27.012 --> 09:28.278
I'm so sorry.

09:28.312 --> 09:32.683
When you hurt, I hurt.

09:32.717 --> 09:33.651
What happened next?

09:33.685 --> 09:34.785
- Whoa.
- [Sighs]

09:34.819 --> 09:36.486
- We made it.
- Everyone okay?

09:36.521 --> 09:37.855
- I'm alive.
Both: Square.

09:37.889 --> 09:39.990
- Guys, knock it off.
- Okay, still alive?

09:40.025 --> 09:41.692
Okay, we're all safe.

09:41.726 --> 09:42.726
We just have to figure out

09:42.727 --> 09:45.562
how to get back to Greendale.

09:45.596 --> 09:46.964
But we're in the middle
of the woods.

09:46.998 --> 09:48.098
Where do we start?

09:48.133 --> 09:49.099
We need to split
into two groups,

09:49.134 --> 09:50.100
the survivors and the others.

09:50.135 --> 09:51.635
Where's the manifest?

09:51.670 --> 09:53.303
Oh, stop it
with your <i>Lost</i> references.

09:53.337 --> 09:54.571
We need to get back home.

09:54.605 --> 09:56.006
What if we're stuck here?

09:56.041 --> 09:57.440
We need to start
a prison system.

09:57.475 --> 09:59.309
We'll be stranded here forever,

09:59.343 --> 10:00.711
and I've never seen
blue man group!

10:00.745 --> 10:02.780
Guys, guys,
we're gonna make it outta here.

10:02.814 --> 10:04.648
We gotta relax.
We're all gonna be fine.

10:04.683 --> 10:05.716
- [Groans]
All: Ahh!

10:05.750 --> 10:06.984
What is that?

10:07.018 --> 10:08.018
I just want to say,
if we're gonna die,

10:08.053 --> 10:09.386
I love you guys.

10:09.420 --> 10:11.822
- I love you all too.
- I did see blue man group.

10:11.856 --> 10:13.356
I just didn't get it.

10:13.391 --> 10:15.458
Why can't they talk?
They have so much in common.

10:15.493 --> 10:18.929
[Groaning and nervous sighing]

10:18.963 --> 10:20.230
- [Hisses]
- Others!

10:20.264 --> 10:21.765
- Huh?
- [Hisses]

10:21.800 --> 10:22.966
[Clears throat] Oh!

10:23.001 --> 10:24.501
[Laughs] I'm sorry.

10:24.535 --> 10:25.602
[Clears throat]

10:25.636 --> 10:26.603
I didn't mean
to startle anybody.

10:26.637 --> 10:27.671
[Laughs]

10:27.706 --> 10:29.472
And I thought my hair
looked fake.

10:29.507 --> 10:32.109
Oh, you guys are a long,
long way from Greendale.

10:32.143 --> 10:34.311
How did you know
we're from Greendale?

10:34.345 --> 10:35.579
Oh, from Pierce's shirt.

10:35.613 --> 10:37.514
How did you know
my name is Pierce?

10:37.548 --> 10:39.316
It's embroidered
on your Greendale shirt

10:39.350 --> 10:40.650
you got at the student store.

10:40.685 --> 10:42.686
How'd you know I got it
at the student store?

10:42.721 --> 10:44.922
- I'm a touch psychic.
All: Oh! Huh. Hm.

10:44.956 --> 10:47.424
Anyway, I used to go
to Greendale just like you guys

10:47.458 --> 10:49.159
before I came out here
to be free.

10:49.194 --> 10:52.096
So this is
how Greendale graduates end up:

10:52.130 --> 10:54.198
As transient mountain men.

10:54.232 --> 10:56.066
Huh.
Not as bad as I thought.

10:56.101 --> 10:57.968
But don't you miss
having stuff?

10:58.002 --> 11:00.971
Out here,
you have everything you need.

11:01.005 --> 11:03.673
And you can be
whoever you wanna be.

11:03.708 --> 11:04.942
All: Huh.
Oh.

11:04.976 --> 11:06.810
♪ Here in the woods ♪

11:06.845 --> 11:08.645
♪ you're totally free ♪

11:08.679 --> 11:10.513
♪ you can live off the land ♪

11:10.548 --> 11:12.515
♪ and be who you want to be ♪

11:12.550 --> 11:14.718
Both: ♪ We can be
our own men ♪

11:14.753 --> 11:16.987
♪ and I don't need an "A" ♪

11:17.021 --> 11:20.758
♪ the perfect mom pressure
would all go away ♪

11:20.792 --> 11:22.993
♪ Greendale is crazy ♪

11:23.027 --> 11:25.262
- ♪ And so is that moose ♪
- Hi, Troy.

11:25.296 --> 11:29.199
♪ Greendale turns
people's screws so loose ♪

11:29.234 --> 11:32.736
♪ we're no exception
to tell you the truth ♪

11:32.771 --> 11:35.105
♪ which is why the woods
is perfect ♪

11:35.140 --> 11:36.774
♪ for all of you ♪

11:36.808 --> 11:40.710
♪ being socially conscious
can be really tough ♪

11:40.745 --> 11:42.746
Ah.
♪ Here in the woods ♪

11:42.781 --> 11:45.215
♪ you can forget
all that stuff ♪

11:45.250 --> 11:47.284
♪ I don't like the pressure ♪

11:47.318 --> 11:49.552
♪ to always be cool ♪

11:49.587 --> 11:51.021
♪ I was gonna sing that ♪

11:51.055 --> 11:53.356
♪ now I don't have a rhyme ♪

11:53.391 --> 11:55.125
♪ we all try our hardest ♪

11:55.160 --> 11:57.027
♪ but the pressure in college ♪

11:57.061 --> 11:59.196
♪ sometimes gets
so tremendous ♪

11:59.230 --> 12:01.265
♪ that it would be stupendous ♪

12:01.299 --> 12:05.435
♪ to be free far away ♪

12:05.469 --> 12:09.739
Both: ♪ From Greendale ♪
- Mm, ooh, yummy.

12:09.774 --> 12:11.708
♪ I really love these berries ♪

12:11.742 --> 12:14.377
♪ where are they from? ♪

12:14.412 --> 12:16.880
♪ my hand just made a rainbow ♪

12:16.915 --> 12:18.916
- ♪ And my-- ♪
- ♪ Magic, magic ♪

12:18.950 --> 12:22.019
♪ well, these magical berries ♪

12:22.053 --> 12:23.987
♪ put us
in a drug seq-- ♪

12:24.022 --> 12:25.856
♪ They make everything swirly ♪

12:25.890 --> 12:28.658
♪ whoa, that bush
sounds like Shirley ♪

12:28.693 --> 12:30.627
All: ♪ Now we're free ♪

12:30.661 --> 12:33.730
♪ far away ♪

12:33.764 --> 12:35.966
♪ from Greendale ♪

12:36.000 --> 12:38.101
Be free, my friends.

12:38.136 --> 12:41.504
- ♪ From Greendale ♪
- Be free.

12:41.539 --> 12:44.741
[Sighs]

12:44.775 --> 12:46.543
Simply inspiring.

12:46.577 --> 12:48.378
Ten minutes ago,
you weren't even speaking.

12:48.412 --> 12:50.347
And now, you've admitted
that a strange man

12:50.381 --> 12:52.649
hand-fed you
psychotropic berries.

12:52.683 --> 12:53.951
This is
puppet therapy work--

12:53.985 --> 12:55.752
Dean! There is a fire
in the cafeteria.

12:55.786 --> 12:58.488
Garrett, <i>not now!</i>

12:58.522 --> 13:00.523
[Groans]
[Chuckles]

13:00.558 --> 13:02.359
Where was I?
Ah! I was healing you.

13:02.393 --> 13:03.827
Hm?
Go on.

13:03.862 --> 13:08.598
Well, those devil berries
freed our minds

13:08.632 --> 13:12.802
and loosened our tongues.

13:12.837 --> 13:16.907
Your skin is so beautiful

13:16.941 --> 13:18.775
and soft.

13:18.809 --> 13:20.443
It's like felt.

13:20.478 --> 13:23.947
[Overlapping relaxed dialogue
and sighing]

13:23.982 --> 13:25.182
I feel so free out here,

13:25.216 --> 13:26.750
like I'm my own man.

13:26.784 --> 13:28.618
If Jeff said
we had to live out here,

13:28.652 --> 13:30.020
I'd totally be down with that.

13:30.054 --> 13:31.889
[Sighing]
Me too.

13:31.923 --> 13:33.690
Can I tell you guys a secret?

13:33.724 --> 13:36.559
Yeah, sure.
[Overlapping dialogue]

13:36.594 --> 13:38.996
I was at the grocery store
with my kids,

13:39.030 --> 13:42.366
and I thought I saw Andre
walk by with another woman.

13:42.400 --> 13:44.501
I love women.

13:44.535 --> 13:46.303
- Mm.
- [Sighs]

13:46.337 --> 13:48.338
I'm gonna go take a growler.

13:48.373 --> 13:51.208
Anyway, I wanted
to follow Andre and the woman,

13:51.242 --> 13:53.176
so I left my kids
at the magazine stand

13:53.211 --> 13:55.078
for just a minute, but somehow,

13:55.113 --> 13:57.214
I lost track of time
and ended up tailing them

13:57.248 --> 13:58.982
all the way out of town.

13:59.017 --> 14:01.118
It wasn't even Andre.

14:01.152 --> 14:04.454
The horrible part is
I forgot my kids

14:04.488 --> 14:08.225
and left them all night
in the grocery store.

14:08.259 --> 14:11.194
[Down-tempo music]

14:11.229 --> 14:18.501
♪ ♪

14:18.536 --> 14:22.139
Well, there y'all go,
giving me that look,

14:22.173 --> 14:24.341
treating me like Judas,

14:24.409 --> 14:27.077
judging me like Judy.

14:27.111 --> 14:30.280
You know, Judge Judy.
She judges people.

14:30.315 --> 14:33.183
Shirley, this is the first
I've heard of you

14:33.217 --> 14:34.918
leaving your kids
in a grocery store.

14:34.953 --> 14:35.986
Me too.

14:36.020 --> 14:37.287
I have no memory
of you saying that.

14:37.322 --> 14:38.655
Well, if you don't know
my secret,

14:38.689 --> 14:40.657
why have we all been
so awkward around each other?

14:40.691 --> 14:43.026
I thought everyone heard
my secret.

14:43.061 --> 14:45.028
I didn't hear you say anything.

14:45.063 --> 14:47.764
So nobody else heard
my terrible secret

14:47.798 --> 14:50.800
about how I...

14:50.835 --> 14:53.870
trail off from time to time?

14:53.904 --> 14:55.738
Did everyone here
reveal a secret?

14:55.773 --> 14:57.174
All: Mm-hmm.

14:57.208 --> 15:00.444
And no one remembers
anyone else's, including mine?

15:00.478 --> 15:01.678
All: Mm-mm.

15:01.712 --> 15:03.680
Those berries
made us real talky

15:03.714 --> 15:05.682
but not real listen-y.

15:05.716 --> 15:08.885
So if no one heard or remembers

15:08.919 --> 15:11.288
anything anyone else said...

15:11.322 --> 15:12.755
Both: We're in the clear.

15:12.790 --> 15:14.491
- ♪ We're in the clear ♪
- I'm a genius!

15:14.525 --> 15:16.259
- ♪ We're in the clear ♪
- Yeah!

15:16.294 --> 15:20.197
♪ We're in the clear ♪
[Overlapping dialogue]

15:20.231 --> 15:22.788
Um, guys?

15:34.428 --> 15:36.320
Um, don't mind me.

15:36.889 --> 15:38.757
I'm sure you guys
can get on with your lives

15:38.791 --> 15:42.427
without the worst mom ever.

15:42.461 --> 15:44.619
[Exhales]

15:45.115 --> 15:46.916
Sounds good.
Anyone up for a movie?

15:46.950 --> 15:48.484
Abed, sit.

15:48.518 --> 15:51.354
Shirley, you have nothing
to be ashamed of.

15:51.388 --> 15:54.257
No one thinks you're a bad mom.

15:54.291 --> 15:57.593
Thanks, Jeff, but I'm--
I'm just gonna go home now.

15:57.627 --> 15:59.028
Shirley, wait.

15:59.062 --> 16:02.464
I think I know how to make
you feel a little less horrible.

16:02.499 --> 16:04.459
I like where you're headed.
Okay, who's holding?

16:04.501 --> 16:05.501
I have four berries,

16:05.535 --> 16:07.203
but I am saving them
for Laser Floyd.

16:07.237 --> 16:10.072
No, we all need
to re-share our secrets sober.

16:10.107 --> 16:11.274
Oh, God.

16:11.308 --> 16:13.776
Look, we were all
feeling crappy earlier,

16:13.810 --> 16:15.711
but at least we were
feeling crappy together.

16:15.745 --> 16:17.380
Shirley is alone now.

16:17.414 --> 16:19.615
This is the only way to put us
on equal footing,

16:19.649 --> 16:22.218
and if it makes it any easier,

16:22.252 --> 16:23.286
we can use these puppets.

16:23.320 --> 16:24.720
- Ah, yay!
- Shut up.

16:24.754 --> 16:27.423
Okay.

16:27.457 --> 16:29.892
I found the perfect girl
for me,

16:29.927 --> 16:31.593
and then, I met her kid.

16:31.628 --> 16:34.230
♪ I said it didn't bother me ♪

16:34.264 --> 16:37.233
♪ But truthfully it did ♪

16:37.267 --> 16:39.235
♪ I promised him I'd make it ♪

16:39.269 --> 16:42.638
♪ to a baseball game he had ♪

16:42.672 --> 16:45.441
♪ But I bailed
and never called again ♪

16:45.475 --> 16:49.478
♪ And now
I'm just exactly like my dad ♪

16:55.352 --> 16:57.586
♪ I am an activist ♪

16:57.620 --> 17:00.756
♪ That's always been
my choice ♪

17:00.790 --> 17:02.691
♪ Truth is I've never voted ♪

17:02.725 --> 17:05.428
♪ Except when I watch <i>The Voice ♪</i>

17:05.462 --> 17:08.364
♪ I was struggling in history ♪

17:08.397 --> 17:11.334
♪ I'm normally the best ♪

17:11.367 --> 17:13.469
♪ I let Cornwallis
rub my feet ♪

17:13.502 --> 17:19.641
♪ to give me all the answers
to a test ♪

17:19.675 --> 17:21.643
♪ I caused ♪

17:21.678 --> 17:25.681
♪ the Greendale fire ♪

17:25.714 --> 17:30.353
♪ of '03 ♪

17:30.387 --> 17:32.654
♪ 55 acres ♪

17:32.689 --> 17:35.824
♪ went up in a blaze ♪

17:35.859 --> 17:40.562
♪ All because I burned
an ant hill ♪

17:40.597 --> 17:43.499
All: ♪ This secret
inside me ♪

17:43.533 --> 17:46.068
♪ was trapped beyond a doubt ♪

17:46.103 --> 17:53.142
♪ and now my most
terrible secret's out ♪

17:53.176 --> 17:54.910
There you are.

17:54.944 --> 17:57.246
Come on, guys.

17:57.280 --> 18:02.584
♪ I've never slept
with the great Eartha Kitt ♪

18:02.619 --> 18:07.890
♪ We dry humped inside
of her tour bus ♪

18:07.924 --> 18:10.626
All: ♪ This secret
inside me ♪

18:10.693 --> 18:13.062
♪ was trapped beyond a doubt ♪

18:13.096 --> 18:20.002
♪ and now my most
terrible secret's out ♪

18:23.973 --> 18:25.174
[Exhales]

18:25.208 --> 18:27.276
I wanna thank you all
for being so open,

18:27.310 --> 18:30.413
and honest, and for syncing
your mouth and hand movements.

18:30.447 --> 18:33.749
And now,
for my most terrible secret.

18:33.783 --> 18:35.817
I am not what you would
call traditionally--

18:35.852 --> 18:38.054
Wait, Abed,
you never told us your secret.

18:38.088 --> 18:39.388
- Oh.
- That's right.

18:39.423 --> 18:40.489
I didn't share one that night.

18:40.524 --> 18:41.924
After we got back
from the woods,

18:41.958 --> 18:43.992
everyone was being silent
and not making eye contact.

18:44.027 --> 18:46.328
I didn't know why,
so I mirrored your behavior.

18:46.363 --> 18:47.463
Both: Oh.

18:47.497 --> 18:49.298
- Mm.
- [Giggles]

18:49.332 --> 18:50.933
Thank you, Jeff,

18:50.967 --> 18:52.967
and I don't think you're
anything like your father.

18:52.969 --> 18:54.703
I don't know
how you take care of one kid,

18:54.737 --> 18:55.904
let alone three.

18:55.939 --> 18:58.941
Aw.
That's nice.

18:58.975 --> 19:01.677
So nobody thinks
I'm a slutty cheater?

19:01.711 --> 19:02.945
All: No.

19:02.979 --> 19:05.281
- Or me as a criminal?
All: No.

19:05.315 --> 19:06.782
[Laughs]

19:06.816 --> 19:10.586
Nobody respects me any less
as a political activist, right?

19:10.620 --> 19:13.055
Well, uh...

19:15.492 --> 19:17.326
the level
to which we respect you

19:17.360 --> 19:20.196
as a political activist
has definitely not changed.

19:20.230 --> 19:21.430
- [Sighs]
- That's right.

19:21.465 --> 19:22.598
- That's how I would say it.
- Exactly.

19:22.632 --> 19:23.999
Whew.
Bye, Dean.

19:24.033 --> 19:25.834
- Bye-bye.
Both: Bye, Dean.

19:25.868 --> 19:28.837
[Overlapping dialogue]

19:28.871 --> 19:31.507
Knowledge is a party.

19:31.541 --> 19:34.443
Once again,
I help fix everyone's problems

19:34.478 --> 19:36.945
only to go home alone.

19:36.980 --> 19:39.948
Who says you have to be alone?

19:41.951 --> 19:43.051
Jeffrey.

19:52.739 --> 19:55.377
Okay--excuse me.
What are we doing here?

19:56.510 --> 19:57.810
Both: Yeah.

19:57.844 --> 19:59.645
[Scatting]

19:59.680 --> 20:01.647
No, Gollum, no!

20:01.682 --> 20:03.182
Are we ready?
Gonna take it from--from--

20:03.216 --> 20:04.850
Take it from your line, Chevy.

20:04.884 --> 20:06.686
♪ Do do do, do do do ♪

20:06.720 --> 20:08.020
Oh, yeah.

20:08.054 --> 20:09.054
♪ ♪

20:09.088 --> 20:10.356
[Punch sound effect]

20:10.390 --> 20:11.657
♪ ♪

20:11.692 --> 20:13.726
Ohh!
Oh, it's happening.

20:13.760 --> 20:16.228
Dance, Shirley.
Dance, girl.

20:16.262 --> 20:19.064
♪ Do do do do do ♪

20:19.098 --> 20:21.200
- There's so much skin!
- Aah!

20:21.234 --> 20:22.868
[Laughing]

20:22.902 --> 20:25.604
Ah, this
is the best thing ever.

20:25.639 --> 20:27.673
♪ Do do do, do do do ♪

20:27.708 --> 20:28.774
♪ do do do ♪

20:29.312 --> 20:31.546
So much skin came off!
[Laughter]

20:31.580 --> 20:34.082
What happened?
Did he knock it off?

20:34.116 --> 20:36.117
What'd I miss?

